member.summary:
Utility method for performing API requests that retrieve data in a consistent manner.
The given request will be performed, and if the response is an outright success then the response data will be unwrapped and returned.
If the call is not an outright success, but the status code is among the other acceptable results (provided via validStatusCodes), the getValueForStatusCode method will be called to generate a return value. This allows the caller to return null or an empty list as desired.
If neither of the above is possible, an exception will be thrown.
